{"cells":[{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["# Grouping Objects by Similarity using k-means\n","\n","Clustering is an unsupervised learning technique used to find groups of similar objects. **k-means** is a highly popular, computationally efficient, prototype-based clustering algorithm. Each cluster is represented by a prototype, which is usually the **centroid** (the average of similar points) or the **medoid** (the most representative point).\n","\n","One of the main drawbacks of k-means is that you must specify the number of clusters, $k$, *a priori* (beforehand).\n","\n","### The k-means Algorithm Steps\n","\n","1. Randomly pick $k$ centroids from the examples as initial cluster centers.\n","2. Assign each example to the nearest centroid.\n","3. Move the centroids to the center of the examples that were assigned to it.\n","4. Repeat steps 2 and 3 until the cluster assignments do not change or a user-defined tolerance/iteration maximum is reached.\n","\n","### 1. Generating a Toy Dataset\n","\n","To visualize how k-means works, we can start by generating a two-dimensional dataset."],"metadata":{"id":"lfjyVNIMc4sk"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["from sklearn.datasets import make_blobs\n","import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n","\n","# Generate a dataset of 150 points roughly grouped into 3 regions\n","X, y = make_blobs(n_samples=150,\n","                  n_features=2,\n","                  centers=3,\n","                  cluster_std=0.5,\n","                  shuffle=True,\n","                  random_state=0)\n","\n","# Plot the unlabelled dataset\n","plt.scatter(X[:, 0], X[:, 1], c='white', marker='o', edgecolor='black', s=50)\n","plt.xlabel('Feature 1')\n","plt.ylabel('Feature 2')\n","plt.grid()\n","plt.tight_layout()\n","plt.show()"],"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}],"execution_count":12,"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":487},"id":"TjZPwfBwc4sm","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1782119181967,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":542,"user":{"displayName":"Gobisan Ananthanadarajan","userId":"08370486503672403873"}},"outputId":"949574cf-b0df-452e-e489-e64f517f4dac"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["### 2. Measuring Similarity and Objective Function\n","\n","Similarity in k-means is often defined as the opposite of distance. For continuous features, the **squared Euclidean distance** is commonly used:\n","\n","$$d(\\mathbf{x}, \\mathbf{y})^2 = \\sum_{j=1}^{m} (x_j - y_j)^2 = \\|\\mathbf{x} - \\mathbf{y}\\|_2^2$$\n","\n","The k-means algorithm is an optimization problem that minimizes the within-cluster **sum of squared errors (SSE)**, also called **cluster inertia**:\n","\n","$$SSE = \\sum_{i=1}^{n} \\sum_{j=1}^{k} w^{(i,j)} \\|\\mathbf{x}^{(i)} - \\boldsymbol{\\mu}^{(j)}\\|_2^2$$\n","\n","*(Where $\\boldsymbol{\\mu}^{(j)}$ is the centroid for cluster $j$, and $w^{(i,j)} = 1$ if the example $\\mathbf{x}^{(i)}$ is in cluster $j$, or $0$ otherwise).*"],"metadata":{"id":"-RyfJmxtc4sm"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["from sklearn.cluster import KMeans\n","\n","# Applying k-means clustering\n","km = KMeans(n_clusters=3,\n","            init='random',\n","            n_init=10,\n","            max_iter=300,\n","            tol=1e-04,\n","            random_state=0)\n","\n","y_km = km.fit_predict(X)\n","\n","# Visualizing the clusters and centroids\n","plt.scatter(X[y_km == 0, 0], X[y_km == 0, 1], s=50, c='lightgreen', marker='s', edgecolor='black', label='Cluster 1')\n","plt.scatter(X[y_km == 1, 0], X[y_km == 1, 1], s=50, c='orange', marker='o', edgecolor='black', label='Cluster 2')\n","plt.scatter(X[y_km == 2, 0], X[y_km == 2, 1], s=50, c='lightblue', marker='v', edgecolor='black', label='Cluster 3')\n","\n","plt.scatter(km.cluster_centers_[:, 0], km.cluster_centers_[:, 1], s=250, marker='*', c='red', edgecolor='black', label='Centroids')\n","\n","plt.xlabel('Feature 1')\n","plt.ylabel('Feature 2')\n","plt.legend(scatterpoints=1)\n","plt.grid()\n","plt.tight_layout()\n","plt.show()"],"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}],"execution_count":13,"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":487},"id":"LM3txKYrc4sn","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1782119182337,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":372,"user":{"displayName":"Gobisan Ananthanadarajan","userId":"08370486503672403873"}},"outputId":"01f8fd5e-abbc-49d0-b206-8325e2a488bf"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["---\n","\n","## Smarter Initialization: k-means++\n","\n","Standard k-means randomly places initial centroids, which can result in bad clustering or slow convergence. **k-means++** solves this by placing initial centroids far away from each other via a weighted probability distribution. Scikit-learn's `KMeans` uses `init='k-means++'` by default.\n","\n","---\n","\n","## Hard vs. Soft Clustering\n","\n","* **Hard Clustering:** (e.g., k-means) assigns each example to exactly *one* cluster.\n","* **Soft Clustering:** (e.g., Fuzzy C-means / FCM) assigns an example to one or more clusters based on a probability weight.\n","\n","In FCM, the objective function includes a fuzziness coefficient ($m$):\n","\n","\n","$$J_m = \\sum_{i=1}^{n} \\sum_{j=1}^{k} w^{(i,j)^m} \\|\\mathbf{x}^{(i)} - \\boldsymbol{\\mu}^{(j)}\\|_2^2$$\n","\n","The cluster membership probability is calculated as:\n","\n","\n","$$w^{(i,j)} = \\left[ \\sum_{c=1}^{k} \\left( \\frac{\\|\\mathbf{x}^{(i)} - \\boldsymbol{\\mu}^{(j)}\\|_2}{\\|\\mathbf{x}^{(i)} - \\boldsymbol{\\mu}^{(c)}\\|_2} \\right)^{\\frac{2}{m-1}} \\right]^{-1}$$\n","\n","---\n","\n","## Finding the Optimal Number of Clusters\n","\n","### 1. The Elbow Method\n","\n","Since we rarely know the true number of clusters, we use intrinsic metrics like SSE (inertia) to evaluate performance. The **elbow method** plots the distortion against $k$. The \"elbow\" is the point where distortion begins to increase much less rapidly."],"metadata":{"id":"NAbfbGAcc4sn"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["# The inertia is readily accessible\n","print(f'Distortion: {km.inertia_:.2f}')\n","\n","# Running k-means for k=1 to 10 to find the elbow\n","distortions = []\n","for i in range(1, 11):\n","    km = KMeans(n_clusters=i,\n","                init='k-means++',\n","                n_init=10,\n","                max_iter=300,\n","                random_state=0)\n","    km.fit(X)\n","    distortions.append(km.inertia_)\n","\n","plt.plot(range(1, 11), distortions, marker='o')\n","plt.xlabel('Number of clusters')\n","plt.ylabel('Distortion')\n","plt.tight_layout()\n","plt.show()"],"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Distortion: 72.48\n"]},{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}],"execution_count":14,"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":504},"id":"GkltnJrac4sn","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1782119182867,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":529,"user":{"displayName":"Gobisan Ananthanadarajan","userId":"08370486503672403873"}},"outputId":"d6238075-8b6c-4d0d-f744-51776276ff25"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["### 2. Silhouette Plots\n","\n","A **silhouette plot** evaluates how tightly grouped the examples are in their clusters. It bounds the silhouette coefficient between -1 and 1. An ideal cluster has a coefficient close to 1.\n","\n","The silhouette coefficient ($s^{(i)}$) combines cluster cohesion ($a^{(i)}$) and cluster separation ($b^{(i)}$):\n","\n","\n","$$s^{(i)} = \\frac{b^{(i)} - a^{(i)}}{\\max\\{b^{(i)}, a^{(i)}\\}}$$"],"metadata":{"id":"npQZ4jrkc4so"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["import numpy as np\n","from matplotlib import cm\n","from sklearn.metrics import silhouette_samples\n","\n","# Re-fit a good model with k=3\n","km = KMeans(n_clusters=3, init='k-means++', n_init=10, max_iter=300, tol=1e-04, random_state=0)\n","y_km = km.fit_predict(X)\n","\n","cluster_labels = np.unique(y_km)\n","n_clusters = cluster_labels.shape[0]\n","silhouette_vals = silhouette_samples(X, y_km, metric='euclidean')\n","\n","y_ax_lower, y_ax_upper = 0, 0\n","yticks = []\n","\n","for i, c in enumerate(cluster_labels):\n","    c_silhouette_vals = silhouette_vals[y_km == c]\n","    c_silhouette_vals.sort()\n","    y_ax_upper += len(c_silhouette_vals)\n","    color = cm.jet(float(i) / n_clusters)\n","\n","    plt.barh(range(y_ax_lower, y_ax_upper), c_silhouette_vals, height=1.0, edgecolor='none', color=color)\n","    yticks.append((y_ax_lower + y_ax_upper) / 2.)\n","    y_ax_lower += len(c_silhouette_vals)\n","\n","# Plot the average silhouette score\n","silhouette_avg = np.mean(silhouette_vals)\n","plt.axvline(silhouette_avg, color=\"red\", linestyle=\"--\")\n","\n","plt.yticks(yticks, cluster_labels + 1)\n","plt.ylabel('Cluster')\n","plt.xlabel('Silhouette coefficient')\n","plt.tight_layout()\n","plt.show()"],"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}],"execution_count":15,"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":487},"id":"_2k3HD_pc4so","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1782119183432,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":558,"user":{"displayName":"Gobisan Ananthanadarajan","userId":"08370486503672403873"}},"outputId":"8e07ca40-b078-43b4-f615-e589862c4fb8"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["### Suboptimal Clustering Example\n","\n","When k-means is applied with an inappropriate number of clusters (for instance, forcing $k=2$ on a dataset that naturally has 3 distinct groupings), the resulting silhouette plot will reflect this poor fit.\n","\n","In a suboptimal clustering scenario, the silhouette plot typically shows:\n","\n","* **Visibly different lengths and widths:** The clusters are no longer uniform in size or density.\n","* **Suboptimal coefficients:** Some points might have silhouette coefficients much lower than the average, indicating they are not a great fit for their assigned cluster.\n","\n","This visual disparity in the silhouette plot serves as strong evidence of a relatively bad, or at least suboptimal, clustering choice."],"metadata":{"id":"O7w7oW5NkSNQ"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["km = KMeans(n_clusters=2,\n","            init='k-means++',\n","            n_init=10,\n","            max_iter=300,\n","            tol=1e-04,\n","            random_state=0)\n","y_km = km.fit_predict(X)\n","plt.scatter(X[y_km == 0, 0],\n","            X[y_km == 0, 1],\n","            s=50, c='lightgreen',\n","            edgecolor='black',\n","            marker='s',\n","            label='Cluster 1')\n","plt.scatter(X[y_km == 1, 0],\n","            X[y_km == 1, 1],\n","            s=50,\n","            c='orange',\n","            edgecolor='black',\n","            marker='o',\n","            label='Cluster 2')\n","plt.scatter(km.cluster_centers_[:, 0],\n","            km.cluster_centers_[:, 1],\n","            s=250,\n","            marker='*',\n","            c='red',\n","            label='Centroids')\n","plt.xlabel('Feature 1')\n","plt.ylabel('Feature 2')\n","plt.legend()\n","plt.grid()\n","plt.tight_layout()\n","plt.show()"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":487},"id":"gc6wBhvVlCED","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1782119183820,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":387,"user":{"displayName":"Gobisan Ananthanadarajan","userId":"08370486503672403873"}},"outputId":"7f28fef8-540a-4258-f5f2-5f68965ee65d"},"execution_count":16,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["cluster_labels = np.unique(y_km)\n","n_clusters = cluster_labels.shape[0]\n","silhouette_vals = silhouette_samples(\n","    X, y_km, metric='euclidean'\n",")\n","y_ax_lower, y_ax_upper = 0, 0\n","yticks = []\n","for i, c in enumerate(cluster_labels):\n","    c_silhouette_vals = silhouette_vals[y_km == c]\n","    c_silhouette_vals.sort()\n","    y_ax_upper += len(c_silhouette_vals)\n","    color = cm.jet(float(i) / n_clusters)\n","    plt.barh(range(y_ax_lower, y_ax_upper),\n","             c_silhouette_vals,\n","             height=1.0,\n","             edgecolor='none',\n","             color=color)\n","    yticks.append((y_ax_lower + y_ax_upper) / 2.)\n","    y_ax_lower += len(c_silhouette_vals)\n","silhouette_avg = np.mean(silhouette_vals)\n","plt.axvline(silhouette_avg, color=\"red\", linestyle=\"--\")\n","plt.yticks(yticks, cluster_labels + 1)\n","plt.ylabel('Cluster')\n","plt.xlabel('Silhouette coefficient')\n","plt.tight_layout()\n","plt.show()"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":487},"id":"qlC6K93okXG9","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1782119184206,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":385,"user":{"displayName":"Gobisan Ananthanadarajan","userId":"08370486503672403873"}},"outputId":"6d799fe6-ee6f-4032-f2f7-cd15ec86180f"},"execution_count":17,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"code","source":[],"metadata":{"id":"TgHJ_nKSktft","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1782119184221,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":12,"user":{"displayName":"Gobisan Ananthanadarajan","userId":"08370486503672403873"}}},"execution_count":17,"outputs":[]}],"metadata":{"colab":{"provenance":[]},"kernelspec":{"display_name":"Python 3","name":"python3"}},"nbformat":4,"nbformat_minor":0}